Program: Outlook
Title: Outlook Inspirations Awards 2016
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03zlbk7
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 5 Jul 2016
For Outlook's 50th birthday, our three distinguished judges name the guests whose actions have moved them, shaken them, or thrilled them most. Natalia Ponce de Leon, Dorris Francis and Kees Veldboer are named as the winners. Matthew Bannister and Jo Fidgen present the Outlook Inspirations Awards 2016. The judges are Nunu Ntshingila, who is head of Facebook for Africa, the Indian actor, director and social activist Nandita Das and the BBC's chief international correspondent Lyse Doucet. Outlook presenters Matthew Bannister and Jo Fidgen host this edition live from the BBC's Radio Theatre with music from Afla Sackey and Afrik Bawantu. Show less